---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'WordPress vs AI Website Builders: Should You Switch?';
const description = 'WordPress powers 40% of websites. AI builders are the new trend. Should you switch from WordPress to AI?';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">COMPARISON</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">WordPress vs AI Website Builders</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        WordPress is the established giant. AI builders are the upstarts. When should you use which?
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Stick with WordPress</strong> if you need content marketing, complex functionality, or have an existing WordPress site.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        <strong>Switch to AI</strong> if you're starting fresh and want a site in 30 seconds without technical knowledge.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- My Experience -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-honey-50 to-yellow-50 border-[3px] border-honey-300 p-6 md:p-8" style="--tw-gradient-to-br: from-amber-50 to-yellow-50; border-color: rgb(252 211 77 / 1);">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: The Content Site Where WordPress Won, But AI Won First</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A blogger wanted to build an affiliate site. 50 articles planned, SEO-focused, monetized with affiliate links. Question: WordPress or AI builder?</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>AI builder route:</strong> Used Durable AI. Generated site in 3 minutes. Launched same day. Month 1: Wrote 5 articles manually, got 120 visitors, earned $8 in affiliate revenue. Site was live fast but WordPress SEO would have been better.</p>

          <div class="bg-amber-100 border-l-[4px] border-amber-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-medium"><strong>The switch to WordPress:</strong> Month 3, migrated to WordPress. Installed Yoast SEO, optimized properly. Month 4-6: Wrote 15 more articles, traffic grew to 850 visitors/month, earned $87 in revenue. WordPress SEO was dramatically better.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The brutal truth:</strong> AI builder got her to launch fast. But for content sites, WordPress's superior SEO tools matter. She lost 2 months of SEO growth by starting with AI builder.</p>

          <div class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-[4px] border-yellow-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> If content marketing (blog + SEO) is your primary strategy, start with WordPress. The SEO advantage is too significant to ignore. AI builders are great for landing pages and portfolios, but WordPress still wins for content-heavy sites.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The middle ground:</strong> 10Web AI gives you WordPress with AI generation. Best of both - WordPress power + AI speed. For content sites, this is often the optimal choice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Middle Ground: 10Web</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <strong>10Web AI</strong> gives you WordPress with AI generation. Best of both worlds:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>AI generates the initial site</li>
        <li>WordPress powers the backend</li>
        <li>Use any WordPress plugin</li>
        <li>Full WordPress flexibility</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        label="Try 10Web (WordPress + AI)"
        className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
